external_knowledge:
- "fired more than 50 arrows" refers to players who have taken more than 50 shots; 
- "masters of their scoring techniques" signifies players with high average points per shot; 
- "quantity and quality of their shots" refers to the total number of shots and the average points scored per shot.

sql:
SELECT AVG(attendance) AS average_attendance
FROM games
WHERE strftime('%Y-%m', date) = '2023-10';

external_knowledge:
- "exceptional marksmanship" refers to a high percentage of successful shots;
- "significant number of attempts" in this context means at least 100 shots;
- "leading players" are those who rank at the top based on the shot success rate.

sql:
SELECT AVG(points) AS average_points, COUNT(*) AS total_shots
FROM shots
WHERE game_id = 0;
